solutions.content:
Here the main idea is we take all words from paragraph and store it into a map with its frequency. Here I inserted only those words which are not in banned array.

Algorithm :
* we first take a unordered_set<string>ban, where I inserted all banned elements so that I can get them in O(1) complexity.
* Then take a unordered map of string as a key and integer as its value.
* Then run a loop on paragraph
		* if current character is a uppercase letter then substract 32 in it to make it lowercase(since we need lowercase words).
		* if current letter is a alphabet then add it to a temporary string.
		* otherwise if that temp is not banned then increase frequency in map. Here I am also maintaining a maximum frequency variable.

* Now traverse to map and if a words frequency equals to maxfrequency then return it.
```
class Solution {
public:
    string mostCommonWord(string paragraph, vector<string>& banned) {
        unordered_set<string>ban;
        unordered_map<string,int>fre;
        for(int i=0;i<banned.size();i++)
            ban.insert(banned[i]);
        string temp="";
        int maxfre=0;
        for(int i=0;i<paragraph.size();i++){
            if(paragraph[i]>64 && paragraph[i]<91)
                paragraph[i]+=32;

            if(paragraph[i]>96 && paragraph[i]<123)
                temp+=paragraph[i];
            else{
                if(!temp.empty() && ban.find(temp)==ban.end())
                {
                    fre[temp]++;
                    maxfre=max(maxfre,fre[temp]);
                }
                temp="";
                continue;
            }
        }
        if(!temp.empty()){
            fre[temp]++;
            maxfre=max(maxfre,fre[temp]);
        }
        for(auto it=fre.begin();it!=fre.end();it++){
            if(it->second==maxfre)
                return it->first;
        }
        return "";
    }
};
```
