solutions.content:
# Intuition
 Letters occurance  

# Approach
Check count for the 'BALON' inspite of 'BALLOON'

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(N) where N is size of string
- Space complexity:
O(1) as using constant space

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int maxNumberOfBalloons(String text) {
        //Store the result in only five size int array as below
        //BALLOON
        //0122334
        int balloon[]= new int[5];

        //Base case, for BALLON as string it should be atleast six letter size
        if(text.length()<6) return 0;

        //Check for each char and get it decided with switch case in faster way
        for(char k:text.toCharArray()){
            switch(k){
                case 'b': balloon[0]++; break;
                case 'a': balloon[1]++; break;
                case 'l': balloon[2]++; break;
                case 'o': balloon[3]++; break;
                case 'n': balloon[4]++; break;
            }
        }

        // Keep occurance of letter 'L' and 'O' as one,
        // so that finally for a single found, each char occurance of BALLON would be 'BALON'
        // by changing 2 repetition of letter 'L' and 'O' into one by below statements
        balloon[2] /=2;
        balloon[3] /=2;

        // If any of the occurance for letter 'L' and 'O' is zero or negative,
        // means there is no atleast one available 'BALLON'
        if(balloon[2]<=0 || balloon[3]<=0) return 0;

        // Assume the first char occurance as min possible 'Ballon' in input string
        int min = balloon[0];

        // Compare it with rest and choose the minimum
        for(int i=1;i<5;i++)
            if(balloon[i]<min)
                min = balloon[i];

        // If min value is negative or zero, means there is no atleast one available 'BALLON'
        if(min<=0) return 0;

        // Otherwise, return the min value for which input string contains min 'BALLON'
        return min;
    }
}
```

