solutions.content:
First let's calculate and save how many ways we can arrive to destination starting from i, j.
For example for [2, 3] k = 1
our dp will look like
10 6  3  1 
 4  3  2  1 
 1  1  1  1 
 starting from 0,0 if ```dp[i][j] >= k``` we will go to right until `dp[i][j] < k` then we go down.
```
class Solution {
public:
    string kthSmallestPath(vector<int>& d, int k) {
        int n = d[0], m = d[1];
        string res;
        vector<vector<int>> dp(n + 1, vector<int> (m + 1, 1));

        for (int i = n - 1; i >= 0; i--)
            for (int j = m - 1; j >= 0; j--)
                dp[i][j] = dp[i][j + 1] + dp[i + 1][j];

        for (int j = 0, i = 0; j < m || i < n;) {
            if (dp[i][j] >= k && j < m) {
                res.push_back('H');
                j++;
            }
            else {
                if ((k -= dp[i][j]) > 0) // else we are on the final column so we dont have to decrement value of j
                    j--, res.pop_back();
