Edit 
I started with brute force `dfs` at the beginning (Not knowing `k` can go to a very high number).  Then I realized that we don't have to generate all those combinations. So I decided to start from the destination save how many ways we can reach to destination from [i, j]. So we will avoid `k - 1` ways and looking for `k`th route.

