        int chance = ncr(total - 1, v);
		// If we have 3 H and 2 V, totally we have ncr(5,2)=10 combinations, if first one is H, then all the combination has ncr(4, 2) = 6. So if K is bigger than it, means first one should be V. otherwise first letter is H.

        if (k <= chance) {
            return "H" + find(h - 1, v, k);
			// if we ignore the first letter, then we have 2 H and 2 V left, run the function again to find it.
        } else {
            return "V" + find(h, v - 1, k - chance);
			// if first one is V, then we need remove the ncr(4, 2) combinations of k. Since we need find the other 4 letters order.
