# Intuition
Since, the path string can only have 2 characters : 'H' and 'V', We can incrementally try to build the path string. Also, the fact that, out of 'total' possible strings, some 'num' strings will start from 'H', and remaining 'total' - 'num' will start from 'V' can help us here.

# Approach
Notice, that you can straightaway tell, that how many number of 'H' (hNum) and how many number of 'V' (vNum) will be in any path. Notice examples carefully for understanding this point.
Next,
Start building answer from index 0.
If k is less than or equal to the number of strings that start with 'H', then first character of our answer will be 'H', otherwise it will be 'V'.
Accordingly update the value of 'hNum' and 'vNum' and k. Repeat this process until 'hNum' and 'vNum' are both not 0.

You can understand how to calculate number of strings starting from 'H' by observing the code.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
In the while loop, either vNum is being decremented each time or hNum is being decremented each time. O(m+n) where m is vNum and n is hNum.
Combination function takes O(min(m,n)) in the worst case.
Final Time Complexity : O((m+n)*min(m,n))

- Space complexity:
No additional space used, apart from few variables.
Final Space Complexity : O(1)

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:

    long long combination(int n,int k) { // calculates (nCk)
        long long res = 1;
        if (k > n - k)
            k = n - k;
        for (int i = 0; i < k; ++i) {
            res *= (n - i);
            res /= (i + 1);
        }
        return res;
    }

    int findStringsStartWithH(int hNum, int vNum) { // finds how many strings starts with 'H' when no.(H) = hNum, no.(v) = vNum
        return combination(hNum+vNum,hNum) * hNum / (hNum+vNum) ;
    }

    string kthSmallestPath(vector<int>& destination, int k) {
        int vNum = destination[0], hNum = destination[1];
        string path = "";
        while(hNum || vNum) {
            int HStrings = findStringsStartWithH(hNum,vNum);
           if(k<=HStrings) {
                path+='H';
                hNum--;
            }
            else {
                path+='V';
                vNum--;
                k -= HStrings;
            }
        }
        return path;
    }
};
```

