solutions.content:
Here as 'V'>'H', placement of 'V' determines the lexicographical rank.

Ex: V=3,H=3,k=18.Now we have 6 places and 3V's to arrange in 6C3 ways=20 ways.
So rank can range from 1 to 20. 1 being lexicographically smallest .

**[ I ]recur(3 H,3 V,rank 18)**
if first V is placed at index=3,
_ _ _V _ _  , rank=1, because remaining 2 V's will be placed in 2 blanks to left
if first V is placed at index=2,
_ _ V _ _ _,then we have 3 blanks, and 2 V's to arrange.Rank will range from 2 to 4 (1+3C2 )
if first V is placed at index 1,
_V_ _ _ _, then we have 4 blanks anf 2 V's to arrange. Rank will range from 5 to 10 (4+4C2)
if first V is placed at index 0,
V _ _ _ _ _, then we have 5 blanks and 2 V's to arrange. Rank will range from 11 to 20 (10+5C2).

To get rank  k=18,we need to place V at index 0. Now we have 5 blanks, 2 V's and we need to get rank=18-10=8. So we  do recursive call to dfs(3 H ,2 V, rank 8)

**[ II ]recur(3 H,2 V,rank 8)**
Here rank can range from 1 to 5C2=1 to 10.
if first V is placed at index=3,
_ _ _ V _ , rank=1 beacuse remaining 1 V will be placed at blank at left.
if first V placed at index=2,
_ _ V _ _, then we have 2 blanks, and 1 V to arrange.Rank will range from 2 to 3 (1+2C1 )
if first V is placed at index 1,
_V_ _ _, then we have 3 blanks anf 1 V's to arrange. Rank will range from 4 to 6 (4+3C1)
if first V is placed at index 0,
V _ _ _ _, then we have 4 blanks and 1 V's to arrange. Rank will range from 7 to 10 (7+4C1).

To get rank=8, we need to put V at index 0. Now we have 4 blanks 1 V and rank=8-6=2.

**[III] recur( 3 H, 1 V, rank=2)**
As we are left with 1 V, rank is directly determined by index of V. To get rank=2, we need to place V at before last index  _ _ V _.

So we place V at index=0,1,4 and rest are 'H'. To get rank 18.

**Base conditions,**
1.if only 1 V left, then place it accordingly to required rank.
2.If rank 1 is required ,then arrange all V's from last index.

Here combination array is used to compute nCr. as nCr= n-1Cr-1 * n/n-r. 
```
class Solution {
    char[] ch;
    public String kthSmallestPath(int[] destination, int k) {
        int H=destination[1],V=destination[0];
        ch=new char[H+V];Arrays.fill(ch,'H');
        recur(H,V,k);
        return new String(ch);
    }
    private void recur(int H,int V,int k){
        //Combination array from r-1Cr-1 to n-1Cr-1
        if(V==1) ch[ch.length-k]='V';
        else if(k==1) while(V-->0) ch[ch.length-1-V]='V';
        else{
            int len=(H+V)-(V-1),r=V-1;
            int[] comb=new int[len];
            comb[0]=1;
            for(int i=1;i<len;i++) comb[i]=(comb[i-1]*(r+i))/i;
            for(int i=1;i<len;i++) comb[i]+=comb[i-1];
            for(int i=0;i<len;i++){
                if(k<=comb[i]){
                    ch[ch.length-(i+r+1)]='V';
                    recur(H,V-1,k-comb[i-1]);
                    break;
                }
            }
        }        
    }
}
