solutions.content:
To get to the **destination(row, col)**, we can only take down step or right step. 
**The total step is (row + col) with row "V" steps and col "V" steps;**  
In those (row + col) oprations, we have to chose row's operation to take down steps and the left are all right steps; 
The total possibale methods is nCr(row + col, row); We have to find kth smallest. 

Obviously, the smallest must start with "H", the largerst must start with "V";
For example with destination (2, 3), 2hen the first character is H, H**** represent  smallest nCr(2+3-1,2) combination. 
when k <nCr(2+3-1,2), the first character must be "H" otherwise it is "V";
we can iterative fill the string;
```
class Solution {
public:
    string kthSmallestPath(vector<int>& des, int k) {
        int row = des[0], col = des[1];
        vector<vector<int>> comb(31, vector<int>(31, 0));
        comb[0][0] = comb[1][0] = comb[1][1] = 1;
        for(int i=2; i<=30;i++)  
            for(int j=0;j<=i;j++)
            {
                if(j==0||j==i)
                    comb[i][j] =1;
                else
                    comb[i][j] = comb[i-1][j] + comb[i-1][j-1];
            }
        return fill(row, col, comb, k);
    }
    string fill(int row, int col, vector<vector<int>>&comb, int k)
    {

        if(k==1||row==0||col==0)
            return string(col,'H') + string(row, 'V');
        if(k==comb[row+col][row])
            return string(row, 'V') + string(col, 'H');
        if(k<=comb[row+col-1][row])
            return "H" + fill(row, col-1,comb, k);
        else
            return "V" + fill(row-1, col, comb, k-comb[row+col-1][row]);
    }
};
